The following background data on cholera in Thailand were extracted
from GIDEON <http://www.GideonOnline.com>
Year(s) Cases
1950-1969 19 739
1973 844
1974 1475
1975 1355
1976 6
1977 383
1978 4183
1979 1788
1980 4331
1981 39
1982 638
1983 1497
1984 645
1985 899
1986 213
1987 6353
1988 2248
1992 6139
1994 3487
Infection by _Vibrio cholerae_ O139 was first reported in 1993
[incidence not available.
"Although no cases of cholera have been officially reported since
1994, the disease has been confirmed in travelers returning from
Thailand to other countries (ie, Hong Kong during 1998; Japan during
1999)."
--
Stephen A. Berger, M.D.
Tel Aviv University, Israel
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
[Thanks to Steve once again for sending us this disease incidence
